CORE GAME LOOP

Every game of Ledger follows the same loop.

Players continuously cycle through:

Build → Earn → Invest → Negotiate → Defend → Expand → Eliminate → Win

The game intentionally changes feeling as it progresses.

Early game is about growth.

Mid game is about competition.

Late game is about survival.

This makes every match feel like it naturally evolves rather than repeating the exact same actions every round.

STARTING A MATCH

Each player begins with:

20 LC
No assets
No loans
No investments
Financial Health: Healthy

The market begins stocked with every asset class.

Players begin taking turns.

PLAYER TURN

Every turn follows the exact same structure.

Step 1

Collect income.

Every owned asset automatically pays its income.

Example

Player owns

King

Queen

Jack

Income

+20
+15
+10

Player automatically receives

+45 LC

No button required.

Income is instant.

Step 2

Pay taxes.

Taxes are automatically deducted.

Taxes are based on

Assets owned
Wealth

Taxes scale naturally.

Rich players pay more.

Poor players pay less.

Taxes keep money circulating.

Step 3

Player chooses actions.

A player can perform actions in any order.

Possible actions:

Buy Asset

Sell Asset

Auction Asset

Negotiate

Invest

Borrow

Repay Loan

Hostile Takeover

Sell to Bank

End Turn

ACTIONS
BUY ASSET

Purchase directly from market.

Pay full purchase cost.

Immediately receive ownership.

Asset begins producing income next round.

SELL TO PLAYER

Players may negotiate privately.

Seller chooses price.

Buyer accepts or declines.

Trade happens instantly.

AUCTION

Player selects asset.

Sets minimum bid.

Auction becomes visible to everyone.

Other players place bids.

Highest bidder wins.

Seller may cancel auction before accepting a winning bid if no final confirmation has occurred (depending on final implementation).

SELL TO BANK

Emergency option.

Bank always buys.

Price:

50% of purchase price.

This exists only as a desperation mechanic.

Players lose value.

INVEST IN PLAYER

Any player may invest.

Investment terms are completely negotiated.

Example

100 LC

Repay 120

Repay after 5 rounds

10% future profits

Anything players agree to.

Game records the contract automatically.

Failure to repay creates legal grounds.

BORROW FROM BANK

Players may borrow.

Maximum:

120 LC

Interest:

50%

Borrow 100

Repay 150

Repayment deadline:

3 rounds

Only one active bank loan at a time.

REPAY LOAN

Repay remaining balance.

Loan disappears.

Financial Health improves.

FINANCIAL HEALTH

Every player always has a visible financial status.

Healthy

Stable

Stressed

Critical

This is determined automatically.

Factors include:

Debt

Cash

Income

Missed payments

Default history

It gives every player an immediate understanding of their financial situation.

MARKET

The market contains four asset classes.

Jack

Queen

King

Ace

Each asset has:

Purchase Price

Income

Tax

Maximum Ownership

Example

Asset	Buy	Income	Tax	Max
Jack	30	+10	2	4
Queen	50	+15	3	3
King	80	+20	2	
Ace	120	+30	1	

(Awaiting final balancing.)

WHY ASSET LIMITS EXIST

Without limits,

One player buys every Ace.

Economy dies.

Nobody catches up.

Ownership caps force diversification.

Players build different portfolios.

Every match becomes unique.

NEGOTIATION

Negotiation is one of Ledger's biggest mechanics.

Players can negotiate:

Asset sales

Investments

Loans

Emergency funding

Takeover defense

Joint legal cases

Future repayment

Everything except taxes.

Negotiation occurs through:

Voice Chat

Text Chat

Trade Window

The game itself enforces the contract.

Nobody can scam someone after accepting.

PRIVATE DEALS

Only participating players can see negotiation.

Others cannot.

This allows

Alliances

Politics

Bluffs

Secret funding

Emergency rescues

Backroom deals

TAKEOVERS

Takeovers are the biggest event in Ledger.

A takeover is not random.

It is earned.

Requirements

Minimum Wealth

120 LC

Takeover Filing Fee

40 LC

Cooldown

3 rounds

Target Immunity

4 rounds after surviving.

STARTING A TAKEOVER

Player pays filing fee.

Chooses target.

Court announces:

Hostile Takeover Initiated.

Everyone sees it.

The target now has ONE ROUND to survive.

DURING DEFENSE

The defending player may:

Borrow

Sell Assets

Auction Assets

Receive Investments

Negotiate

Sell to Bank

Repay Debt

Anything legal.

Every player now decides

Help them?

Or let them die?

This creates incredible social moments.

WIN CONDITION FOR DEFENDER

The defender must satisfy ONE objective.

Reach a required LC reserve before their next turn.

(The exact reserve value is dynamically calculated by game rules rather than requiring players to manually calculate percentages.)

This keeps calculations invisible.

Players only see:

Target Required

Current Progress

Simple.

IF DEFENDER SURVIVES

Takeover fails.

Attacker permanently loses filing fee.

Target becomes immune.

Everyone celebrates.

The table changes.

IF DEFENDER LOSES

Player is eliminated.

Their remaining liquid assets are liquidated.

Attacker receives:

One selected asset of their choice

plus

A small liquidation reward.

Not enough to snowball.

Enough to justify the risk.

WHY THIS SYSTEM WORKS

Takeovers are expensive.

Risky.

Rare.

Exciting.

Nobody casually launches them.

But everybody fears them.

Exactly what we wanted.

BANKRUPTCY

Players become bankrupt if:

Cannot repay bank loan.

Cannot pay taxes.

Cannot survive takeover.

Cannot recover finances.

When bankrupt:

Player eliminated.

Assets liquidated.

Contracts closed.

Investments settled where possible.

GAME ERAS

Ledger naturally changes throughout one match.

Era One

Foundation

Everyone grows.

Everyone buys assets.

Economy expands.

Little conflict.

