WHAT WINNING SHOULD FEEL LIKE

Winning Ledger should feel earned.

Not lucky.

Not random.

Not accidental.

The winner should finish the game thinking:

"I outplayed everyone."

Not

"I got lucky."

WHAT LOSING SHOULD FEEL LIKE

This is extremely important.

Players should never lose and think:

"The game cheated me."

Instead, they should think:

"I know exactly where I messed up."

Maybe they borrowed too much.

Maybe they trusted the wrong person.

Maybe they expanded too quickly.

Maybe they launched a takeover too early.

Maybe they were too passive.

Every loss should teach.

That's how players improve.

THE RICHEST PLAYER SHOULD NEVER FEEL SAFE

Most economy games fail because once someone becomes rich...

...the game is over.

Ledger rejects this philosophy.

Being rich gives power.

But it also paints a target on your back.

Everyone watches the leader.

Everyone negotiates against them.

Everyone prepares to stop them.

Being rich should feel rewarding...

...and dangerous.

THE POOREST PLAYER SHOULD NEVER FEEL HOPELESS

This is equally important.

A poor player should always have options.

